  "doc_id": "46382",
  "text": "Additionally, the short communication range between aerial robots, and unmanned aerial vehicles in general, is interesting from the point of view of security. In fact, this short range communication may avoid communication jamming, which is a significant threat in the practical application of unmanned aerial vehicles ( [CITATION_1] ). Therefore, in this paper we focus the synchronization problem in teams of aerial robots (ARs), but the results are applicable to general multirobot systems.",
